### Dart: Managing Game State for Opponent and Game Over

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2023-02-14-flutter-real-time-multiplayer-game.mdx

This Dart code snippet defines methods critical for real-time game state management. The `updateOpponent` method processes incoming network data to dynamically adjust the opponent's position and health, scaling coordinates relative to the screen size. The `endGame` method is responsible for setting the game's final state when either the player or opponent runs out of health, triggering a callback to signal the conclusion of the match.

```dart
  void updateOpponent({required Vector2 position, required int health}) {
    _opponent.position = Vector2(size.x * position.x, size.y * position.y);
    _opponent.updateHealth(health / _initialHealthPoints);
  }

  /// Called when either the player or the opponent has run out of health points
  void endGame(bool playerWon) {
    isGameOver = true;
    onGameOver(playerWon);
  }
}
